    "format": "(UINT16) Game type\r\n(UINT16) Length\r\n(STRING) Data\r\n",
    "remarks_html": "<p>Response for both <a href=\"/packet/102/sid-optionalwork\">S&gt;C 0x4A SID_OPTIONALWORK</a> and <a href=\"/packet/182/sid-requiredwork\">S&gt;C 0x4C SID_REQUIREDWORK</a>. See <a href=\"/document/43/extrawork\">ExtraWork</a> document for more details.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Game type</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><code>0x01</code></td>\n<td>Diablo II</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>0x02</code></td>\n<td>Warcraft III</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>0x03</code></td>\n<td>Starcraft</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>0x04</code></td>\n<td>World of Warcraft; reason for this is not known, but most recent libraries have included it</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Length: Likely the length of the <em>Data</em>, in number of bytes.</p>\n<p>Data: A string usually containing computer information.</p>",
